<%# Phase 37 Wave A1 (landscape redesign, 2026-05-19) — channel ID card.
    2026-05-19 follow-up — card resized to 226 × 358 px and five
    visual enhancements applied (see `id_card_component.rb` class
    comment): name padding all sides, avatar spacing + larger size,
    handle centered under avatar, footer + lower hairline now scoped
    to the right column only (left column extends full body height,
    avatar grows to 150 px), stat grid column order flipped so the
    trend arrow lives at the right edge. The outer card stays a
    vertical flex container; the bottom area is no longer
    full-width — it's nested inside the right column instead. %>
<article class="channels-id-card"
         data-channel-id="<%= channel[:id] %>"
         style="display: flex; flex-direction: column;
                width: <%= card_width_px %>; height: <%= card_height_px %>;
                flex: 0 0 <%= card_width_px %>;
                border: 1px solid var(--color-cover-border);
                border-radius: 2px;
                background: var(--color-channel-id-card-bg);">

  <%# Row 1 — name, full width across the top. Bold weight at body 13 px. 2026-05-19 follow-up: padding bumped to 6 px vertical / 8 px horizontal so the title has visible breathing room from the top + bottom hairline and from the left/right card borders (was 2 px uniform — too tight per user screenshot). %>
  <div class="channels-id-card__name"
       style="padding: 6px 8px;
              font-weight: 700;
              max-width: 100%;
              white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">
    <%= channel[:display_name] %>
  </div>

  <%# Horizontal hairline between name and body. Spans the full card
      width (this is the only horizontal hairline that still does so;
      the lower hairline below the stats is right-column-only per
      Enhancement 4). %>
  <div class="channels-id-card__hairline"
       style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); width: 100%;"></div>

  <%# Row 2 — body. Two columns split by a vertical hairline. Left
      column now extends through the full body height (no in-column
      bottom hairline, no full-width footer underneath it). Right
      column stacks the stat grid on top + a hairline + the footer
      below. Body fills the remaining vertical space via `flex: 1`. %>
  <div class="channels-id-card__body"
       style="display: flex; flex: 1; min-height: 0;">

    <%# Left column — avatar (centered) + handle below (centered under
        the avatar per Enhancement 3). `align-items: center` centers
        both children horizontally inside the column; the bracketed
        `[handle]` link inherits that centering. `padding: 6px 4px`
        gives the avatar extra breathing room from the top hairline
        and the card's bottom edge (Enhancement 2: "more spacing in
        the avatar and the hairlines that surround it"). `padding-
        left: 10px` adds the requested extra left margin (4 px base
        + 6 px extra). `gap: 8px` between avatar and handle is the
        same Enhancement-2 breathing increment. %>
    <div class="channels-id-card__left"
         style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;
                padding: 6px 4px 6px 10px;
                align-items: center;
                width: 125px; flex-shrink: 0;
                box-sizing: border-box;">
      <%# Avatar — circular per design.md §"Channel avatars". `margin-
          top: 3px` nudges the avatar ~3 px lower so it visually centers
          within its bound area (avatar tile + 8 px gap + handle row)
          instead of hugging the top hairline (user screenshot 2026-05-
          19 — top of avatar was sitting too high). %>
      <% if channel[:avatar_url].present? %>
        <img src="<%= channel[:avatar_url] %>"
             alt="<%= channel[:display_name] %>"
             class="channels-id-card__avatar"
             style="width: <%= avatar_dimension_px %>; height: <%= avatar_dimension_px %>;
                    flex-shrink: 0;
                    margin-top: 3px;
                    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
                    object-fit: cover;
                    border: 1px solid var(--color-cover-border);
                    border-radius: 50%;
                    display: block;">
      <% else %>
        <span class="channels-id-card__avatar"
              aria-label="<%= channel[:display_name] %>"
              style="width: <%= avatar_dimension_px %>; height: <%= avatar_dimension_px %>;
                     flex-shrink: 0;
                     margin-top: 3px;
                     aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
                     border: 1px solid var(--color-cover-border);
                     border-radius: 50%;
                     display: block;"></span>
      <% end %>

      <%# Handle — centered under the avatar (parent column has
          align-items: center, so this wrapper is auto-centered). The
          ellipsis fallback stays in case the handle is unusually
          wide. %>
      <div class="channels-id-card__handle"
           style="max-width: 100%; text-align: center;
                  white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">
        <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: channel[:handle], href: handle_url)) %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%# Right column — stacked: stat grid on top (fills remaining
        space) + hairline + footer at the bottom. The hairline + footer
        are scoped to this column only (Enhancement 4). The vertical
        hairline between left/right columns is a `border-left` on this
        wrapper so it spans the full body height. %>
    <div class="channels-id-card__right"
         style="display: flex; flex-direction: column;
                border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border);
                flex: 1; min-width: 0;">

      <%# Stat grid — three rows × three columns. Enhancement 5
          column order: `1fr auto auto` → number / unit / arrow. The
          number cell uses `justify-self: end` so the three number
          right edges align at the same x against the unit label.
          The unit cell uses `justify-self: start` so the three unit
          left edges align. The arrow cell uses `justify-self: end`
          so the three arrows align at the right edge. `padding-
          right: 6px` keeps the arrows ~6 px clear of the card border
          (the requested right-margin breathing room). %>
      <div class="channels-id-card__stats"
           style="flex: 1;
                  display: grid;
                  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto auto;
                  column-gap: 6px;
                  row-gap: 4px;
                  align-content: center;
                  padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;
                  min-width: 0;">

        <% glyph, css_var = trend(channel[:subscriber_count_trend]) %>
        <span class="channels-id-card__value"
              style="font-size: <%= stat_value_font_size %>; justify-self: end; align-self: center; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;"><%= subscriber_count_formatted %></span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__label"
              style="color: var(--color-muted); justify-self: start; align-self: center;">subs</span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__trend"
              style="display: inline-block; width: 1em; justify-self: end; align-self: center; color: var(<%= css_var %>);"><%= glyph %></span>

        <% glyph, css_var = trend(channel[:view_count_trend]) %>
        <span class="channels-id-card__value"
              style="font-size: <%= stat_value_font_size %>; justify-self: end; align-self: center; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;"><%= view_count_formatted %></span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__label"
              style="color: var(--color-muted); justify-self: start; align-self: center;">views</span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__trend"
              style="display: inline-block; width: 1em; justify-self: end; align-self: center; color: var(<%= css_var %>);"><%= glyph %></span>

        <% glyph, css_var = trend(channel[:watch_hours_trend]) %>
        <span class="channels-id-card__value"
              style="font-size: <%= stat_value_font_size %>; justify-self: end; align-self: center; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;"><%= watch_hours_formatted %></span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__label"
              style="color: var(--color-muted); justify-self: start; align-self: center;">hours</span>
        <span class="channels-id-card__trend"
              style="display: inline-block; width: 1em; justify-self: end; align-self: center; color: var(<%= css_var %>);"><%= glyph %></span>
      </div>

      <%# Footer — Enhancement 4: scoped to the right column only.
          The hairline above the footer is a `border-top` on this
          element so it sits inside the right column and does not
          extend across the left column. Copy is `[ YouTube Studio ]`
          per the locked rename (brand names always capitalized). %>
      <div class="channels-id-card__studio"
           style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
                  padding: 2px 6px 2px 4px; text-align: right;">
        <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "YouTube Studio", href: studio_url)) %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
